<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Los Angeles Laker Kareem Abdul-Jabbar, who grew
up in New York and went on to become the National Basketball
Association's all-time scoring leader, was honored at his last
scheduled game in his hometown.
   In halftime ceremonies Tuesday night, the 41-year-old six-time
