<2ND_LINE>PM-Northern Ireland, 1st Ld-Writethru, a0484,0345</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Rocket Misses Police Jeeps And Crowded Pub; Destroys Butcher Shop</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: Subs 3 grafs for 6th pvs, ``The officer...'' to UPDATE with
comment from police official. Pickup 7th pvs, ``He said...''</NOTE>
<DATELINE>BELFAST, Northern Ireland (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Guerrillas fired a rocket at two
police jeeps, but missed and demolished a butcher's shop, police
reported.
   A press officer at Belfast police headquarters said the
Soviet-made RPG7 anti-tank rocket just missed a crowded pub when it
was fired Tuesday night in Castlewellan, 25 miles south of Belfast.
No one was injured.
   No group immediately claimed responsibility for the attack, but
suspicion fell on the Irish Republican Army. The mainly Roman
Catholic IRA is fighting to end British rule in predominantly
Protestant Northern Ireland and unite it with the 95 percent
Catholic Republic of Ireland under socialist rule.
   The press officer said on condition of anonymity that the rocket
went through the window of the shop and through two walls at the
back of the building before exploding.
   He said a man who had just left the pub narrowly escaped death
when the rocket passed within a few feet of him. The man's parked
car was damaged in the explosion.
   ``It is a miracle he is alive today,'' Chief Superintendent Alwyn
Harris of the Royal Ulster Constabulary said today. Harris said the
rocket is ``a notoriously indiscrimate and inaccurate weapon'' and
if it had hit the pub, ``we could easily have had a massacre on our
hands.''
   The press officer said the rocket was fired from a house taken
over by two masked men who held three people in the building at
gunpoint while they waited for the police patrol to pass by.
   He said that after the attack, the gunmen fled in a car owned by
the house's owner. The car was later found abandoned.
   The officer said police believe the rocket was supplied to the
IRA by Libya. British authorities have repeatedly alleged that
Libyan leader Col. Moammar Gadhafi has been supplying the IRA with
arms.
</TEXT>
