<HEAD>Train Derails, Severs Natural Gas Line; 450 Evacuated</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LAKELAND, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A freight train derailed early today,
rupturing a natural gas line and forcing the evacuation of 450
people, a state official said.
   No injuries were reported in the accident northwest of here, said
Dick Morgan, spokesman for the state Division of Emergency
Management.
   Police said the train consisted of 184 cars, 25 of which left the
tracks. One of them dug into the ground, rupturing the line, police
said.
   A mile-square area around the site was evacuated.
   The Polk County Sheriff's Office said that the wind was helping
dissipate the gas and that there was little likelihood of an
explosion.
</TEXT>
