<1ST_LINE>r a PM-WhiteStudentGroup     11-23 0300</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-White Student Group,0313</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>White Student Group Recognized By Temple University</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By A.J. HOSTETLER</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>PHILADELPHIA (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Temple University has formally recognized a
student group that promotes white pride, entitling the organization
to a faculty adviser, the use of university facilities and $1,000 a
year in support.
   Temple spokeswoman Kathy Gosliner said Tuesday that officials
recognized the White Student Union after reviewing its application
with a lawyer.
   ``It has nothing to do with whether we agree with what they
believe,'' she said. ``We adhere strongly to principles of free
speech.''
   Michael Spletzer, a 22-year-old senior and architecture major,
said he formed the group to balance what he called the
``pro-minority'' stance taken by Temple with its minority
scholarships, affirmative action program and educational philosophy.
   ``There has never been a voice for the rights and feelings of
whites on campus,'' Spletzer said. He said he is is not a white
supremacist.
   ``The rights of white Americans are being stepped on all over,''
he added.
   Spletzer said the group has 89 members; Ms. Gosliner said said
she did not know how many people are in the White Student Union, but
four people signed the application for recognition. She said the
group must be open to all students.
   Recognition entitles organizations to the use of certain
university facilities, a faculty adviser, the right to be considered
for office space and $1,000 a year for student activities, said
another Temple spokesman, George Ingram.
   Temple NAACP president Vaughn Goodwin expressed concern about the
formation of the group.
   ``For one race to come out and say racial pride of others is just
talk is indirectly indoctrinating racism,'' said Goodwin, a
19-year-old junior majoring in public relations.
   Goodwin said he if WSU activities suggest racism, ``we will take
direct action'' against the group.
</TEXT>
