<HEAD>Cox Says `Family Ties' Cast is Ready to Move On</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Courteney Cox says she's itching to earn a
bad-girl image after wrapping up the final season of ``Family Ties.''
   ``I don't feel like the sweet little girls I play,'' Cox, 24,
said in the December issue of Self magazine.
   ``If anything, I'm a little too old for my age,'' she said. ``I
started working when I was young, I lived on my own, I dated an
older man.''
   When ``Family Ties'' ends after its seventh season, Cox, who
plays Michael J. Fox's girlfriend, will hardly be misty-eyed.
   ``Everyone's ready to move on,'' she said. ``They've written just
about everything you can write about a family.''
   Now, Cox wants to play complex characters.
   ``I'm kind of itching to do a very real drama, something like
``'night, Mother,'' or a romantic lead. I always play the
intellectual, never the sexy or the bad girl.
   ``I don't know if they're going to let Courteney Cox of `Family
Ties' or `Cocoon' play someone with a drug addiction. But I'm
ambitious. I like to get things done and I want to do it now. I'm
very determined,'' she said.
