<HEAD>Frank Tenczar, Emmy Award Winning Television Reporter, Dead At 45</HEAD>
<DATELINE>JERSEY CITY, N.J. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Frank Tenczar, an Emmy-award winning
television reporter, died Tuesday from AIDS-related complications.
He was 45.
   Tenczar, senior reporter for New Jersey Network News, won an Emmy
award in Philadelphia in 1986 for individual achievement and one in
Seattle in 1977 for a groundbreaking documentary on homosexual
lifestyles.
   Tenczar's jobs included stints at WYSL in Buffalo; the ABC radio
network and WNYE-TV in New York; WHCT-TV in Hartford, Conn.; and
WAST-TV in Albany, N.Y.
   He also worked as host and producer of a weekly news magazine on
KING-TV in Seattle.
