<DOCNO> AP881123-0207 </DOCNO>
<FILEID>AP-NR-11-23-88 1949EST</FILEID>
<1ST_LINE>r a AM-Reagan-Indians     11-23 0070</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Reagan-Indians,70</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Reagan Signs Bill To Establish Indian Health Service</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SANTA BARBARA, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   President Reagan signed legislation
Wednesday setting up a separate Indian Health Service within the
U.S. Public Health Service.
   The bill also creates a new Native Hawaiian health professions
scholarship program and authorizes special new pay and bonuses for
the Public Health Service commissioned corps and civilian personnel
who serve in the Indian Health Service.
</TEXT>
