<2ND_LINE>PM-US Sprint,0150</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Announces New System to Speed Call Transmissions</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   US Sprint Communications Co. said today it has
deployed a system of signal enhancements that will speed voice and
data transmissions through its fiber optic network.
   The system will improve call set-up time to put calls through an
average of three seconds faster and improve the company's automated
validation system to increase its ability to detect toll fraud, US
Sprint said.
   The company said the signaling system is critical to its plans to
provide future features and functions of its network. Earlier this
month, US Sprint completed the final segment of its third planned
transcontinental fiber route, so that all calls over its network now
go over fiber.
   US Sprint, a partnership of United Telecommunicationis Inc. of
Kansas City and GTE Corp. of Stamford, Conn., is the nation's
third-largest long-distance telephone company.
</TEXT>
