<HEAD>Chrysler Recalls Some Cars</HEAD>
<DATELINE>HIGHLAND PARK, Mich. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Chrysler Corp. on Wednesday recalled
about 580,000 cars made between 1985 and 1987 because of a fuel-hose
problem.
   The company said all the affected cars have front-wheel-drive and
2.2-liter, turbocharged engines. Chrysler said because of
deterioration and cold weather, the hoses may stiffen and fuel leaks
could occur under the cars' hoods.
   Chrysler, which will fix the problem at no cost to the consumer,
said it knew of no injuries or accidents because of the problem.
</TEXT>
