compared with last week's 91,624 and last year's 48,646.
   Canadian automakers were to build 17,527 cars this week, down
from 17,737 a week ago and down from last year's 22,690.
   Canadian light truck production was scheduled at 21,073, compared
with 22,218 a week ago and 18,337 in the same week last year.
