<1ST_LINE>u f AM-GilletteLayoffs     11-23 0186</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Gillette Layoffs,0192</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Gillette to Close Two Canada Plants</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BOSTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Gillette Canada Inc. will phase out manufacturing
operations in Montreal and Toronto as part of its restructuring
program to increase productivity and strengthen its competitive
position, officials said Wednesday.
   The Montreal facility, which produces blades, razors and toiletry
products, and the Toronto plant, which manufactures writing
instruments and corrective fluids, will be phased out over an
18-month period beginning in early 1989.
   ``The decision has a deep impact on all of us,'' said Ronald J.
Rossi, president of the Blade and Razor Division, North America.
``It will directly affect approximately 430 regular and 100
temporary employees in Montreal and 60 employees in Toronto.''
   Rossi's remarks were included in a statement issued by
Boston-based Gillette Co., the parent company.
   Gillette said that since the restructuring program began in
January 1987, the company has phased out or sold operations in the
United States, Argentina, Brazil, Britain and other countries.
   The company said Gillette Canada will remain a fully independent
operating unit. Sales, marketing, distribution and administrative
functions also will remain in both Montreal and Toronto.
</TEXT>
